<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-280-368  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 280 368.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  March 26 1990 v7 n12 p24(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Micro Logic PIM upgrade adds phone dialer, network support. (MicroLogic Corp. introduces Info Select personal information manager)(product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Micro Logic Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Info Select (Personal information management system) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Software packagesPersonal Information Management SystemsProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>The second generation of Micro Logic Corp.'s inexpensive Tornado personalinformation manager (PIM) has arrived, equipped with an automatic phonedialer, improved network support and a variety of ways to view data.andM;The $99.95 PIM, now called Info Select, allows users to manage and retrieverandom information, but surpasses its competitors by delivering a phonedialer, word-processing and database functions, and the ability to performcomputations, according to James Lewis, president of the Hackensack, N.J.,andO;company.andM;Like Lotus Development Corp.'s Agenda, Info Select offers users a variety ofways in which to retrieve and view data.andP;  Lewis said users can search forwords, phrases, strings of words, ranges of dates, or &quot;fuzzy&quot; matches (whichspecifies retrieving both a key word and its synonyms, for example).andM;Relationships among Info Select items can be created by simply assigningcodes specifying that the items are part of a group.andP;  A hypertext feature inthe software lets users establish ties among windows of data so that allrelated information is retrieved with one keystroke.andM;Micro Logic can be reached at (201) 342-6518 or (800) 342-5930.andO;</TEXT></DOC>